    en: "Bad contractors generate one of the top categories of consumer complaints in Monroe County. A contractor takes a deposit and disappears, does shoddy work, or bills far above the quote. General Business Law Article 36-A (sections 770 through 778) sets the baseline: a written contract with specific terms, a 3-day right to cancel for home-solicited sales, and rules on deposits. A contractor who takes money with no intent to perform can be charged with larceny. Permits and licensing rules are handled at the town level — see the trades entries for each municipality. Complaints run through the NYS Attorney General, the local building department, and, in fraud cases, the police."
